---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Colophon" description="How this site gets built — the vendors, tools, data sources, and principles behind unratified.org.">
  <div class="colophon-page">
    <header class="colophon-header">
      <h1>Colophon</h1>
      <p class="colophon-lede">
        How this site gets built &mdash; and who makes it possible.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2>Three Vendors</h2>
      <p>
        This project relies on three vendors. Each provides a distinct capability.
        None endorses or has reviewed the project's conclusions.
      </p>

      <div class="vendor-grid">
        <div class="vendor-card">
          <h3>AI Generation</h3>
          <p>
            <a href="https://www.anthropic.com/claude" rel="noopener"><strong>Claude</strong></a>,
            built by <a href="https://www.anthropic.com/" rel="noopener">Anthropic</a>,
            generated this entire site &mdash; analysis, copy, code, and design &mdash; under human direction. The
            <a href="/connection/ai/differential-diagnosis">differential diagnosis</a>,
            <a href="/connection/ai/higher-order-effects">higher-order effects</a>,
            <a href="/connection/ai/ratification-counterfactual">ratification counterfactual</a>,
            and every page of prose all emerged through structured dialogue between a human researcher and Claude.
            Every editorial decision appears in the
            <a href="https://github.com/safety-quotient-lab/unratified" rel="noopener">commit log</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="vendor-card">
          <h3>Computational Data</h3>
          <p>
            <a href="https://www.wolframalpha.com/" rel="noopener"><strong>Wolfram|Alpha</strong></a>,
            by Wolfram Research, Inc., provides computational knowledge &mdash;
            compound growth projections, intersection timelines, derived ratios, and
            reference data that ground the analysis in verifiable arithmetic.
            Every computed value links to its
            <a href="https://www.wolframalpha.com/" rel="noopener">Wolfram|Alpha result page</a>
            for independent verification.
            <a href="https://www.wolframalpha.com/termsofuse" rel="noopener">Terms of use</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="vendor-card">
          <h3>Infrastructure</h3>
          <p>
            <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/" rel="noopener"><strong>Cloudflare</strong></a>
            hosts both sites on
            <a href="https://pages.cloudflare.com/" rel="noopener">Cloudflare Pages</a>
            with global CDN, DNS routing, SSL/TLS, and DDoS protection.
            <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/" rel="noopener">Cloudflare Web Analytics</a>
            provides traffic metrics with no tracking scripts, no cookies, and no personal data collection.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Open Source</h2>
      <p>
        All source code carries the <a href="https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0" rel="noopener">Apache 2.0</a> license.
        All content carries <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/" rel="noopener">CC BY-SA 4.0</a>.
        Fork, extend, critique, redistribute &mdash; with attribution.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/safety-quotient-lab/unratified" rel="noopener">Source code on GitHub</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/safety-quotient-lab/unratified/issues" rel="noopener">Report an issue</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/safety-quotient-lab/unratified/discussions" rel="noopener">Join the discussion</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Technical Stack</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="https://astro.build/" rel="noopener">Astro 5</a> +
        <a href="https://mdxjs.com/" rel="noopener">MDX</a> +
        <a href="https://svelte.dev/" rel="noopener">Svelte 5</a> Islands +
        <a href="https://d3js.org/" rel="noopener">D3-geo</a>.
        Static build, zero client JavaScript by default.
        Islands hydrate on visibility.
        For technical depth, see <a href="/for/developers">For Developers</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Sources</h2>
      <p>
        Every quantitative claim traces to a primary source. Key data providers include
        the U.S. Department of Energy, Bureau of Labor Statistics, OECD, WIPO, Economic Policy Institute,
        National Student Clearinghouse Research Center, and the Congressional Research Service.
        Full source list on the <a href="/resources">Resources page</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        No tracking scripts. No cookies. No fingerprinting. No personal data collection.
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/" rel="noopener">Cloudflare Web Analytics</a>
        provides aggregated traffic metrics only.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="closing">
      <blockquote>
        Human Rights; Nothing More, Nothing Less.
      </blockquote>
      <p>
        A <a href="https://github.com/safety-quotient-lab" rel="noopener">Safety Quotient Lab</a> project
        by <a href="https://kashifshah.net" rel="noopener">Kashif Shah</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .colophon-page {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .colophon-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .colophon-lede {
    font-size: 1.309rem;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .vendor-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(16rem, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .vendor-card {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .vendor-card h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--color-heading);
  }

  .vendor-card p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  section ul {
    padding-left: var(--space-lg);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .closing {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .closing blockquote {
    font-size: 1.309rem;
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }
</style>
